retag811515645sd" parent-tag-id="48">pilus</sd-pretag> retraction. When in contact with cells <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1652590762sd" parent-tag-id="61">pili</sd-pretag> can interact through their tips (1) and then along their sides (2). Adhesion of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1255702204sd" type="subcellular" role="component">plasma membrane</sd-pretag> along the side of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1838338730sd" parent-tag-id="61">pili</sd-pretag> mediates one-dimensional wetting and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag559032983sd" type="subcellular" role="component">membrane</sd-pretag> protrusion formation (Charles-Orszag et al., 2018). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75909"/></sd-panel></fig></article>